## Typical Results and Timelines

Professional services SEO operates on realistic timelines. The markets are competitive, the authority-building is methodical, and the results compound:

**Months 1–3:** Technical foundations resolved. Topical map and first content cluster live. Google Business Profile optimised. Initial ranking movements for lower-competition practice area terms and long-tail queries.

**Months 3–6:** Topical authority building across target practice areas. Mid-competition local queries beginning to climb. Practitioner entity authority developing. First measurable increase in organic enquiry volume.

**Months 6–12:** Compound authority growth. Page-one positions for competitive local and regional practice area queries. Organic becomes a consistent, predictable enquiry channel.

**12+ months:** Dominant positions across full practice area content clusters. Organic enquiry volume compounding month-on-month. Content programme has sufficient depth that new competitors face a significant barrier to displace established positions.

One Berkshire professional services client went from invisible in local search to top-3 positions for their core service terms in 5 months — resulting in a 3× increase in monthly enquiries from organic.

